==Academic==
The school has a First Form (Year 7) intake of 3-4 classes; followed by another intake in the Third Form (Year 9) of 2 or 3 classes depending on the cohort's size from the First Form, this results in an average year size of 150, and a sixth form of about 300.The pupil teacher ratio is low be general school standards, and class sizes range start at around twenty to twenty-five in the First Form through to [[GCSE]] and are less than 16 by the final two years.<ref name="preprev">{{cite news |url=http://www.prepreview.com/school/Royal_Grammar_School_Guildford.html |title=Prep Review - RGS Guildford |last=  |first= |year=2006 |work= |accessdate=29 December 2010 |location=}}</ref>

Pupils are required to take at least 10 GCSE subjects during Fourth and Fifth forms, which must include Biology, Chemistry, Physics, Mathematics, English Literature, English Language and a Humanity (History, Religious Studies or Geography).<ref name="schoolweb96">{{cite news |url=http://www.rgs-guildford.co.uk/page_viewer.asp?page=Middle+%28Year+4+and+5%29&pid=28 |title=School Website |last=  |first= |date= |work= |accessdate=29 December 2010 |location=}}</ref> In recent years the school has moved offering the [[iGCSE]] in Maths, Sciences, History and Technology.<ref name="schoolweb95">{{cite news |url=http://www.rgs-guildford.co.uk/page_viewer.asp?page=Public+Exam+Boards&pid=603 |title=School Website |last=  |first= |date= |work= |accessdate=29 December 2010 |location=}}</ref> Boys in the Sixth Form usually take four [[GCE Advanced Level|AS Levels]] and continue with three to [[GCE Advanced Level|A2]] level.<ref name="schoolweb94">{{cite news |url=http://www.rgs-guildford.co.uk/page_viewer.asp?page=Curriculum+%26raquo%3B+Senior+%28Sixth+Form%29&pid=29 |title=School Website |last=  |first= |date= |work= |accessdate=29 December 2010 |location=}}</ref>

RGS is one of the most academic schools in the country. The school enjoys consistent 100% pass rates,<ref name="ccom">{{cite news |url=http://www.charity-commission.gov.uk/SIR/ENDS28/0000312028_SIR_09_E.PDF |title=Charity Comission Charity 302128 SIR |last=  |first= |date= 21 December 2009 |work= |accessdate=29 December 2010 |location=}}</ref> and is consistently one of the top performing schools at both A-Level and GCSE level.<ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.dailymail.co.uk/home/education/schoolResult.html?id=9366534 |title=Daily Mail Independent School League Tables |accessdate=2010-12-20}}</ref> Pupils at the school are very successful at gaining places at both [[University of Oxford|Oxford]] and [[University of Cambridge|Cambridge]] universities, often featuring within the top 20 in the country with regards to number of places awarded.<ref name="telegraph1">{{cite news |url=http://www.telegraph.co.uk/education/universityeducation/8090117/Pupils-from-elite-schools-secure-one-in-ten-Oxford-places.html |title=Pupils from elite schools secure one in ten Oxford places |last= Nick Collins, Becky Ratcliffe and Tom Rowley |first= |date= 28 October 2010 |work= |accessdate=22 December 2010 |location=}}</ref><ref name="times1">{{cite news |url=http://www.timesonline.co.uk/tol/news/uk/education/article2492736.ece |title=Handful of independent schools seize a third of Oxbridge places |last=Woolcock |first=Nicola |date= 20 September 2007 |work= |accessdate=22 December 2010 |location=}}</ref> In the 2009/10 leavers' year, a record 42 boys have received offers from [[Oxbridge]],<ref name="geye1">{{cite news |url=http://www.guildfordeye.com/visitor/news/more.detail/news.php?record_id=288&set=1&cat=Education |title=PRGS Reports Record Oxbridge Results |last=  |first= |date= 4 February 2010 |work= |accessdate=22 December 2010 |location=}}</ref> and the school sends many pupils to other top universities, including [[Durham University|Durham]], [[Imperial College London|Imperial]] and [[University College London|UCL]].<ref name="schoolweb97">{{cite news |url=http://www.rgs-guildford.co.uk/page_viewer.asp?page=Leavers%27+Destinations&pid=405 |title=School Website |last=  |first= |date= |work= |accessdate=29 December 2010 |location=}}</ref>

==School life==
===Terms===
As in most schools in the UK there are three [[Academic term|terms]] in the Academic year:<ref name="sw1">{{cite news |url=http://www.rgs-guildford.co.uk/page_viewer.asp?page=Term+Dates&pid=39 |title=School Website |last= |first= |date= |work= |accessdate=22 December 2010 |location=}}</ref>
* The ''Michaelmas Term'' from early September to mid-December. This is the normal term for new boys to be admitted into the school
* The ''Lent Term'' from early January to a time a week or two before whenever [[Easter]] falls that year
* The ''Trinity Term'' from mid-late April to early July, during which time boys sit most public exams

===House system===
There are six [[House system|houses]] at the RGS, named after various benefactors of the school:

